<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1055</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1070</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17620467/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17620467</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.274065095">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=EGD+%3D+esophagogastroduodenoscopy&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">EGD = esophagogastroduodenoscopy</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IMA+%3D+inferior+mesenteric+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IMA = inferior mesenteric artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPR+%3D+multiplanar+reformatted&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPR = multiplanar reformatted</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PACS+%3D+picture+archiving+and+communication+system&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PACS = picture archiving and communication system</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=RBC+%3D+red+blood+cell&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">RBC = red blood cell</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SMA+%3D+superior+mesenteric+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SMA = superior mesenteric artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=WCE+%3D+wireless+capsule+endoscopy&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">WCE = wireless capsule endoscopy</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">CT angiography has the potential to profoundly impact the evaluation and treatment of patients with acute gastrointestinal bleeding and should be considered as a first-line diagnostic examination in the appropriate clinical setting.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Christopher J.</span> <span property="familyName">Laing</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, MetroHealth Medical Center, Case Western Reserve University, 2500 MetroHealth Dr, Cleveland, OH 44109. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual M